@database MKVINFO
@master "MKVINFO."1""
@remark "manual page source format generated by PolyglotMan v3.2 available at http://polyglotman.sourceforge.net/"
@wordwrap
@tab 8

@node sect0 "Name"
mkvinfo - Print information about tracks in Matroska files 
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
@{b}mkvinfo@{ub} [@{i}options@{ui}] @{i}inname@{ui} 
@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
This program lists all tracks contained in a Matroska file including information about the codecs used. 



À inname @{lindent 3}
Use '@{i}inname@{ui}' as the source. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-g@{ub}, @{b}--gui@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Start the GUI. This option is only available if mkvinfo was compiled with GUI support. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-v@{ub}, @{b}--verbose@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Be verbose and show all Matroska elements. See the section '@{b}VERBOSITY LEVELS@{ub}' for details. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-c@{ub}, @{b}--checksums@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Calculates and display the Adler32 checksum for each frame. Useful for debugging only. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-s@{ub}, @{b}--summary@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Only show a terse summary of what @{b}mkvinfo@{ub} finds and not each element. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}--output-charset@{ub} <@{i}charset@{ui}> @{lindent 3}
Sets the charset to which strings are converted that are to be output. It defaults to the charset given by system's current locale. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-r@{ub}, @{b}--redirect-output@{ub} <@{i}filename@{ui}> @{lindent 3}
Writes all messages to the file @{i}filename@{ui} instead of to the console. While this can be done easily with output redirection there are cases in which this option is needed: when the terminal reinterprets the output before writing it to a file. The charset set with @{b}--output-charset@{ub} is honored. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-h@{ub}, @{b}--help@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Show usage information. @{lindent 0}

À @{b}-V@{ub}, @{b}--version@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Show version information. @{lindent 0}


@endnode

@node sect3 "Verbosity Levels"
The @{b}-v@{ub} option can be used to increase @{b}mkvinfo@{ub}'s verbosity level and print more information about the current file. 



À level 0 @{lindent 3}
will print only the track headers it finds and their types. @{b}mkvinfo@{ub} will exit as soon as the headers are parsed completely (more technical: as soon as the first cluster is encountered). In this level the seek head entries and the cues will not be displayed - even if they're located in front of the track information. @{lindent 0}

À level 1 @{lindent 3}
will also print all Matroska elements encountered for the complete file but the seek head entries and the cue entries. @{lindent 0}

À level 2 @{lindent 3}
will also print the seek head entries, the cue entries and the file position at which each Matroska element can be found at. @{lindent 0}

À level 3 @{lindent 3}
will print some information that is not directly connected to a Matroska element. All other elements only print stuff about the elements that were just found. Level 3 adds meta information to ease debugging (read: it's intended for developers only). All lines written by level 3 are enclosed in square brackets to make filtering them out easy. @{lindent 0}




@endnode

@node sect4 "Author"
@{i}mkvinfo@{ui} was written by Moritz Bunkus <moritz@bunkus.org>. 
@endnode

